HEADWORD: Madrina
<hw>Ma*dri"na</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp., prop., a
godmother.]</ety> <def>An animal (usually an old mare), wearing a bell
and acting as the leader of a troop of pack mules.</def> <mark>[S.
America]</mark>⟦br⟧
